The paper deals with capacity regions of a network under a generalized-delay model, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The network being studied is a multimessage multicast network (MMN), which is a type of network commonly studied in computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the capacity regions for specific types of MMNs, such as those consisting of independent DMCs and wireless erasure networks, which are topics in network information theory (cs.SI). The paper also uses mathematical techniques such as product distributions and achievable rate tuples, which are topics in probability and statistics (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
